<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I would take out validator's arguments out of the option array and have them stick with validor, It would be easier to read and more in line with Zend_Filter_Input</p>

<p>So instead of:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$element-&gt;addValidator('StringLength', false, array(6, 20));
</code></pre>

<p>We could have:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$element-&gt;addValidator(array('StringLength', 6, 20));
</code></pre>

<p>The second argument  could also be the breakChainOnFailure or the option array ?</p>

    </div>
