        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2008-03-05T09:55:20.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>While I appreciate the idea of using a variable number of arguments, this is not a terribly good practice:</p>

<ul><li>If the second argument could be either breakChainOnFailure <em>or</em> a constructor argument, what happens if the constructor allows a boolean as its first argument?</li>
<li>Variable arguments mean IDE signature hinting will not work (many developers use IDEs, and variable arguments mean no helpful tooling)</li>
<li>Having the constructor arguments in an array makes loading from a configuration file easier</li>
</ul>
